pCo: locomotive train person clothing man
content: So yesterday I took a trip to the Bury Transport Museum at to see it s newest exhibit the famous LNER A4 Class 60009 Union of South Africa now on public display after a long career running in preservation It s certainly a sight to see this beautiful machine in the relatively small surroundings of the transport museum surrounded by its excellent collection of cars vans bikes and buses The first thing I noticed is that she stands in stark contrast to her immaculately polished sister 4468 Mallard by still wearing the coat of dirt and soot with heat pealed paintwork after a long career of steaming the permanent way and she looks all the better for it Her exterior has been returned to how she looked to the end of her career for British Rail with the red nameplate and modern warning flashes replaced by black and the classic 1960 s style ones which I really like There s plenty of information on display about Sir Nigel Gresley the LNER and the A4 s for all those that want to find out more and the footplate is readily accessible letting you follow in the footsteps of all those fortunate enough to take hold of the regulator and sit in the comfortable drivers seat to gaze at the mix of 1930s valves and gauges peppered with the modern electronics that enabled her to run on the mainline up until very recently It s well worth a visit to the Transport Museum if you find yourself at the East Lancashire Railway or in Bury You get in free if you ve got a day river ticket or it s 5 if you re just visiting the museum I believe 60009 is on show for at least the next couple of years and it s well worth going along to see this speed machine and one of the 6 A4 s that survived the scrappers torch up close unionofsouthafrica class pacific transportmuseum geek

content: Day 54 60 In loving memory of Gimuy Cairns Naarm Melbourne Kms ran today 71 92kmTotal Kms ran so far 3 601 64kmsCurrently running in Kurnai landToday was really tough I had so little energy all day but I persevered with one foot in front of the other As my legs didn t want to get going and I felt run down I had to really focus on my reasons why I m out there Today was s 50th birthday I dug deep and did my best for you coach I was given a massive lift when and surprised me with a visit to run with me and of course they brought donuts Thanks guys Massive thank you to everyone who has donated to We have currently raised 43 470 50 of our 60 000 fundraising goal If you d like to donate please click the link in my bio Together we can help Make A Wish Australia help critically ill children achieve their number 1 wish When a wish comes true a child discovers that despite their situation anything is possible This is what my run is all about Thank you to my awesome support crew on day 54 smith77Thank you to my sponsors supporters co smith77 Paul Wheelton

content: Surely enough to put you off for life It s our final day here today What a great trip it has been I had my anxieties about 5 of us sharing a room something we ve never done before and how the kids behaviour might impact our holiday Because we co parent the older girls 50 50 we re not used to all being together for longer periods Co parenting is a tricky thing to navigate You spend half your time missing your children whilst enjoying a break and then the remaining time together you re resetting behaviours and dealing with an attack of the senses This is a weekly thing for us We make the most of our situation but it is tricky sometimes It s sad to not have them with me all the time and sometimes hard when we re all together and I m managing 3 small peoples needs It s one extreme to another So this trip has cemented future trips away like this We now know we can do it and we ve all had so much fun together The cherry on the cake for me is whilst managing my struggles with certain things I ve worked through each one of them sober I ve used my internal resources to try and glide through parenting anxieties and I ve proved to myself yet again that I can do anything Now I am just Teri and not relying on wine to cope Teri I can operate perfectly well wine free and feel a deep sense of pride and happiness for cruising through situations the best I can and not numbing them out I really feel like I have come a long way from those initial single mum days several years ago Around that time I never ever thought I d get married have another baby and achieve sobriety I felt so low and worthless back then It s nice to reflect and appreciate the growth Ok now just a day in the sun and a 9 hour journey overnight Have a lush Saturday

content: I ve been asked about this recently and I remember reading about it when at my wits end googling at 3am with my first baby It went like this if your baby falls asleep in your arms and you put them down asleep when they wake up and you aren t holding them it s like waking up on your neighbours front lawn They MUST fall asleep independently supporting them to sleep is likely the reason they are waking at night As a first time mom this made sense I was thinking okay so now I shouldn t nurse or rock to sleep because that s confusing for her Lets try putting her down awake and if I ve nailed the wake window she should just drift off Well you can guess what happened next This is such a bizarre concept so if I fall asleep on the couch and my partner brings me to my bed when I wake up it will feel like I m somewhere else No Just no This is used to push parents into non responsive methods that usually go against their instincts Now if it worked for you that s really great so no need to come at me with defensive comments I really am happy you found something that worked The difficulty is it doesn t work for most babies A baby wakes at night for 87362 reasons hungry wet cold hot scared in pain misses their parent loud noise etc It s not because you nurse rocked or bounced them to sleep Maybe they are 6 months and the longest they can go without a feed is 2 hours that s normal or maybe they are not developmentally ready to link multiple sleep cycles It s not your fault your baby is waking If you rock them to sleep and transfer to their sleep space when they wake and don t need something they will recognize the smells sounds and environment Work on having them LOVE their sleep space Play in the crib during the day hang out in the room sleep on their sheets or spill some breastmilk on them Layer in lots of sleep associations so your baby has lots of ways to fall asleep Rock and sing bounce and shush sing and sway rock sing bum pats That way when something stops working you can make changes to the patterns So remember you are amazing and so is your baby You ve got this

content: This is the best pasta I have made in a MINUTE If you visit my site you ll notice an absence of sun dried tomato recipes Why Because I always found them too tangy Fortunately I am in LOVE with these Sun Dried Tomatoes with Garlic in Olive Oil The flavor is sweet robust and works perfectly in this creamy sauce I used the trifecta of Italian flavors tonight including Dried Italian Oregano and Parmigiano and Bianchetto Truffle Cream Save this post recipe is below 1 tbsp neutral oil 1 yellow onion peeled and sliced 1 4 cup sun dried tomatoes in oil roughly chopped plus 1 teaspoon of the oil 2 tbsp butter 1 tsp dry Italian oregano 1 2 tsp crushed red pepper optional 2 cups water or vegetable stock 1 3 cup mascarpone or heavy cream 8 ounces Tagliatelle 1 tsp truffle cream optional Salt and pepper to taste Heat the oil in a wide pot over medium heat Add the onion and cook stirring regularly for 8 10 minutes until softened Season with salt and pepper Add the chopped sun dried tomatoes and 1 teaspoon tomato oil from the jar Cook 3 4 minutes more Melt the butter into the onions and tomatoes Once frothy add the oregano and crushed red pepper Cook 1 minute Season with salt and pepper Pour in the water or stock and bring to a boil Reduce heat to medium low and hard simmer until thickened about 15 minutes If the sauce reduces too quickly reduce heat to low and add a splash or two more of water Taste and season to your preferences Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil Add the pasta and cook until al dente Scoop out 1 3 cup of the pasta cooking water and set it aside Drain the pasta If using the truffle cream add it to the reserved hot pasta cooking water and stir to temper it Add the mascarpone or heavy cream to the pot of sun dried tomato sauce and bring to a boil Reduce heat to medium and add the reserved pasta cooking water with truffle cream Let the sauce bubble for 5 minutes until thickened Taste and season Add the pasta and cook for 1 2 minutes more until completely coated with the sauce Turn off the heat Divide the pasta between shallow bowls Garnish with parsley Enjoy

content: Life is what you celebrate All of it On 4th June 2022 the happiness quotient at school was at an all time high the reason being our Flag off ceremony for the silver jubilee celebration of our school Dr Sarvepalli Radhakrishnan Vidyalaya Borivali The Flag off was indeed a great way to start all the wonderful celebrations at school The programme took everyone down the memory lane of how the school started and attained laurels and glories Our Principal Ma am Mrs Manisha Arondekar shared the theme for the year Beyond the boundaries and the guiding light for all the students and teachers is Dhruv the constant pole star Our Chairman Sir Shri Vikram Patel our Financial Director Mr Giriraj Khandelwal Sir and our Founder Principal Mrs Asha Damle Ma am addressed everyone on the occasion The joy on everyone s face as our Chairman sir waved the Flag and signalled the flag off with the entire audience joining in waving the flag was a visual treat The day was a perfect start to our silver jubilee celebration so come join us as we begin the fun and excitement the whole year round Special

content: Project Name Woodchester MansionLocation Gloucestershire EnglandProject Type MansionConstruction Started 1858Construction Stalled 1870Current Residents 200 Horseshoe BatsWilliam Leigh and inexperienced architect Benjamin Bucknell began planning the Woodchester Mansion in the late 1850s and construction began in 1858 The massive gothic revival style mansion progressed slowly but steadily over the next decade Unfortunately as William Leigh s health deteriorated progress slowed and by the time Leigh passed away in 1873 construction on the mansion had stopped altogether Leigh s heirs appeared to have little interest in completing the project which began to be neglected In 1938 Leigh s granddaughters sold the incomplete home to a charitable organization who intended to turn the incomplete building into a mental health hospital These plans were canceled as WWII became everyone in Europe s main focus in the 1940s The house continued to sit vacant although remarkably despite being vacant for well over 100 years it never fell into complete disrepair A small group of locals did their best to maintain the building and grounds and in the early 1990s it was bought by a local government organization It now opens the building to the public several months out of the year Several hundred bats began living in the attic in the 1950s and have been the only permanent residents the house has ever had except for all the ghouls and poltergeists that paranormal investigators insist are living in the building too Photo Credits divento craftinvaders nationaltrustuk stroudtimes revival lovers

content: Pagani Zonda 760 Roadster After more than 2 years we can finally reveal probably one of our favourite projects ever May we present the Pagani Zonda 760 Roadster The 5th and final entry into Pagani s iconic 760 series 760 Roadster joins probably the best Pagani collection on the planet with even more to come and it s a pleasure to work with the owner every time LMM Design was given the task by the owner of creating the specification in every detail We are of course a separate entity to Pagani and our plans were handed to them via the owner and executed by the factory You can see here our final plan for the specification which of course had a few changes by Pagani Almost every colour under the sun was considered until finally liquid silver was chosen nearly 1 year after starting the process We knew right away covering the entire car in this paint was the way to go but breaking up the panels with exposed carbon stripes also Another feature also chosen was the use of the sharkfin found on the Zonda 750 which was never actually manufactured This allowed the smaller Cinque wing to be used while also having the classic extreme style of the 760 RS fitting the Roadster style perfectly Wheels come in the form of two toned rims from the HP Barchetta The interior is inspired by Zonda C12 001 featuring two tone tan leather and alcantara Pagani went for a slightly different seat design and brighter white leather There are so many unique details on the car that have never been done before that we simply can t write them all Let us know which ones you spot particularly on the video in slide 5 zonda lifestyle withoutlimits design porn ofinstagram gram tagram gasm cars photography

content: We have 16 pigs Over the years we have saved a total of 18 pigs but we have lost two Bella and Winston We love all of our pigs equally so I try to post about each one but it s a lot of pigs and we also have 8 other species Rest assured EVERYONE at Loving Farm is adored and gets a lot of attention Tonight I want to feature Zachary He was found wandering after one of our local County Fairs Probably because he didn t win a prize so he was dumped We HATE County Fairs Fairs sell themselves as fun family entertainment when in fact they are promoting animal abuse and slaughter The cute animals being shown at fairs are going to be loaded onto slaughter trucks when the fair ends Please don t support County Fairs Zachary was found and saved by two wonderful humans who became our friends and volunteers Their names are Concetta and Moorea We will always be grateful to them Zachary loves his girlfriend Luna and they are always together but this post is about Zachary as an individual He is a very sweet boy He loves his life here at Loving Farm and clearly he loves our muddy pond Zachary will always be safe with us He is important He is unique Please eat plants not pigs It s not healthy or normal to eat pigs Yuck Eating animals is weird and wrong Written byLFAS Co Founder Tracey Jackson Soucy sofinstagram sofig gylove sofinstagram from slaughter dreaming california

content: Can t stop thinking of this image It s literally how my husband and I have been walking the earth for the last almost 15 months without our baby What a cruel curse to have your baby die on their entrance into the world We are that statistic our baby died as a result of a birth injury during labor If only I had known what I know now to go back and advocate for myself and save her If only but that s not a choice because life isn t a game We don t get do overs and the results of the choices made by my provider has led us here broken hearted childless and imagining an alternate life where we hold Verity s hand as she would be waking now and eating and lighting up our lives A devastating shadow and absence of our child is here instead I wouldn t wish this on anyone awareness stillloved shared from

content: Nadine Dorries taking an early morning dip No It s just a 14 foot long tiger pickled and suspended in a tank of As you do Executed in 1991 was commissioned to create The Physical Impossibility of Death in the Mind of Someone Living by It s an icon of late and an emblem of the as an artistic movement for want of a better word and contemporary British culture Punchy yet presentational august yet aristocratic this deliberately disruptive work now belongs to Steve Cohen who between 2007 and 2010 lent it to The Metropolitan Museum of Art What s it about Everything and nothing as is so often the case with Hirst s work I think it s about being confronted by something so fucking terrifying that you d think you d fear for your life yet you don t because as humans we re simply incapable of thinking of and thus comprehending our own demise We all die We all know we re going to die Yet we all live like we won t We can t live our lives any other way thus presents a conundrum death safely incarcerated which neatly embodies the great lie we all live by The terror isn t the shark nor is it the toothy danger it so powerfully symbolises The terror is our failure to accept the volatility of our fickle beginnings the chaos of our agonised middle and the horror of our inexorable end Sounds a bit like the terror bountifully provided by Boris Johnson s Prime Ministership Bit like Nadine s inability to accept its inevitable downfall Damien Hirst celebrates his 57th today ist istsoninstagram

content: So My procedures are done I ate and slept a few hours yesterday because the medication made me feel so high For my Upper endoscopy they took biopsies from my esophagus For the Colonoscopy they found 1 polyp in my colon and 1 polyp in my stomach they will also be sent off for biopsy It was crazy because I was awake the entire time and even asked questions while they were doing it They warned me some people can stay awake There were a few times it got extremely uncomfortable but my nurse talked me through it Overall I thought it was actually pretty cool and I am praying my results are negative Only side effects after procedure was a headache sore throat and some stomach pains Today my throat is still sore and I am very tired For me the worst part was the prep mix just trying to keep it down My results will be take a few weeks They told me to take it easy for a few days and since I have to work today there will be no workout due to extreme fatigue I need my energy for work tonight Instead I am cooking and grocery shopping style y motivation rat life time ness mom life trainers motivation

content: Let s talk about modest fashion Since announcing that I wanted to start a modest fashion journey I have experienced an overwhelmingly beautiful amount of support and also a lot of opinions As with many things the definition of modesty is subjective it will vary from person to person As a Christian modesty for me is about wearing less revealing and or fitted clothing and for me that starts with covering up my chest and rear area I now wear a balance of fitted and tight clothing and whilst I choose to cover up my chest and rear area I still however show other parts of my body such as my arms and stomach Modesty for me was never about simply covering up entirely It s about a balance of change in my fashion choices that I feel are a part of another journey for me my relationship with God I have actually always loved modest fashion by the way and for the first 28 years of my life I often remained somewhat modest with my fashion choices There was a time after 28 where I began experimenting with other style choices however now I have decided to explore the world of modesty once more only this time with more intent It is a journey as is many things and thus far this is modesty for me And if there is anything I ve truly understood so far exploring this world for a second time it is that modest fashion is so so beautiful

content: For anyone saying that the science changed yes empirical science is not perfect You normally find what you are looking for and won t see what you aren t looking for However this is not an excuse when it comes to people s health Science being wrong when it s something superfluous like how the universe was created isn t a problem because it does not have an immediate impact on people When science does have an immediate impact on people we need to be very clear that it s findings are incomplete and build off of each other rather than proving something The biggest thing I learned from my time at university was that you never prove anything We can say there is correlation we can say there is causation but we can never say something is for sure as there s always more information to add

content: The correct answer to this question is FALSE It s actually the opposite Your body stores a tremendous amount of energy calories in the form of fat totaling over a hundred thousand calories for a typical adult In contrast a typical adult only stores about two thousand calories of energy in the form of carbohydrates Most people think of calories as only being in foods but calories are essentially energy Food has energy and our bodies have energy as well Our bodies store nearly all of this FAT energy in our adipose tissue this is the fat underneath your skin and is what you see when you are refer to as wanting to lose fat There are a few other places our bodies store fat as energy but these are trivial when compared to adipose tissue Combined these other caloric fat stores hold less than 2 5 of the total energy stored as fat These other fat stores are inside the muscles in the blood as triglycerides and in the blood as free fatty acids Carbohydrates are mostly stored as glycogen in our muscles with some additional storage in the liver also as glycogen There is also a trivial amount of blood glucose that can be used for energy Knowing we have all this caloric energy stored in our bodies you never have to worry about running out of energy it is impossible

content: I personally recommend you follow for the best and amazing fitness and mindset tips Thanks for all the incredible inspiration FollowFollow THE SKINNYFAT SOLUTION If you re a skinnyfat type of guy or girl chances are you don t have much training experience to begin with Additionally since the body fat is generally high with little muscle mass chances are you don t eat much protein but still eat at a caloric surplus by adding more total carbohydrates and fats Quite infact skinnyfat people identify as such because they have a very small amount of muscle mass Skinny with a high of bodyfat fat The Solution As you may had already guessed protein and resistance training is where the magic happens Skinny fat people are pretty much beginners this means that you can get away with a body recomposition approach aka fat loss muscle building at the same time 1 Strength training progressive Overload You need to focus on getting stronger and lifting heavier weight doing more reps within your sets and progressing 2 Eat plenty of protein and lift heavy weights Protein is the macronutrient that you NEED to increase to build muscle mass This is just as important as step one Your muscle will grow ONLY if you ll give it the right stimulus progressively overloading the bar and the building blocks to make your body adapt to it 1g lb of protein per pound is plenty If you want to speed up the process of fat loss you can even lower your calories slightly Pick a deficit that you can sustain for longer between 15 20 off of your est TDEE and stay there Even if your bodyweight doesn t drop it doesn t necessarioy focus on body composition changes 3 It won t happen over night Focus on the long term and try to make this a priority Stay patient and learn to love the process Find this helpful Share it with your friends Turn on post notifications so you never miss a post By tofit

content: The Midway class was a class of three United States Navy aircraft carriers The lead ship USS Midway was commissioned in September 1945 and decommissioned in 1992 USS Franklin D Roosevelt was commissioned in October 1945 and taken out of service in 1977 USS Coral Sea was commissioned in April 1947 and decommissioned in 1990 The CVB 41 class vessels then unnamed were originally conceived in 1940 as a design study to determine the effect of including an armored flight deck on a carrier the size of the Essex class The resulting calculations showed that the effect would be a reduction of air group size the resulting ship would have an air group of 64 compared to 90 100 for the standard Essex class fleet carriers As it progressed the design also became heavily influenced by the wartime experience of the Royal Navy s armored carriers As a result of study of damage sustained by various British carriers prior to our entry into the war two important departures from traditional U S Navy carrier design were incorporated in the CVB Class then still under development HMS Illustrious in an action off Malta on 1 January 1941 was hit by several bombs three of which detonated in the hangar space Large fires swept fore and aft among parked planes thereby demonstrating the desirability of attempting to confine the limits of such explosions and fires by structural sectionalization of the hangar space On the CVB Class the hangar was therefore divided into five compartments separated by 40 and 50 pound Special Treatment Steel STS division bulkheads extending from the hangar deck to the flight deck each fitted with a large door suitable for handling aircraft Wiki Please follow us on our network https linktr ee shipsandmodelsPD All ships pictures taken from Internet fixed and colorized If you had information about the photographer contact us we will gladly put the name on the credits oftheday

content: Talking honestly about body image and society s perception of older women Emma Thompson admitted that she struggled to look at her own body in the mirror She said The human body is not honestly represented on screen pretty much ever and especially not in my industry I know that I really try to get women to embrace the change that is happening but it has to come from a place of honesty No woman will respond well to toxic positivity just love the body you are in is a hard pill to swallow for many women who see seismic changes through menopause I know I found it hard Emma then detailed that women had been brainwashed about their bodies as she discussed the impact of societal expectations and dishonesty surrounding sex When I m looking in the mirror I m always trying to make myself look better turning this way or that checking out my arse pulling something in Simply revealing my utter incapacity to accept my body as it is But in the movie at that point Nancy s body has just given her these seconds of pure pleasure and she is marvelling at it not it as it looks but it as it has become to her A place she can be happy A place she can find genuine bliss she shared There is a lot of work that needs to be done internally that places a value on ourselves as a person and not simply on how we look Well done Emma for being candid on this topic Taken from an interview with Lorraine and The Times about her new film Good Luck to You

content: Lynk Co Next Day Concept ______________________________________ 6 8 22 Lynk Co the Chinese Swedish brand created by auto giant GEELY who owns Volvo Polestar and has major stakes in Daimler has launched their Next Day concept This 4 door GT concept car takes the existing signatures design and stretches it out a bit adds butterfly doors and a sloping fastback Its a very concept car look but even in production form Lynk Co cars look a bit wild Spec Sheet Under the skin likely is the E Motive power system which sounds quite familiar if you know your Volvo s Upfront is a gas engine to drive the front wheels and out back is an electric motor out back to create a PHEV e AWD system Inside also is a bit crazy with a yoke steering device minimalist theme and zero gravity front seats This whole concept is meant to show off the brand s next generation of design ________________________________________ACN EXTRA I wouldn t mind Lynk Co in the US ________________________________________ Text by allcarnews Images by Lynk Co

content: Question The ancients have told of their experiences their bliss in meditation their super consciousness their holy reality If one may be allowed to ask must one set aside all this and their exalted example Any authority on meditation is the very denial of it All knowledge concepts and examples have no place in meditation The complete elimination of the meditator the experiencer the thinker is the very essence of meditation This freedom is the daily act of meditation The observer is the past his ground is time His thoughts images and shadows are time binding Knowledge is time and freedom from the known is the flowering of meditation There is no system and so there is no direction to truth or to the beauty of meditation To follow another their example or word is to banish truth Only in the mirror of relationship do you see the face of what is The seer is the seen Without the order that virtue brings meditation and the endless assertions of others have no meaning whatsoever they are totally irrelevant Truth has no tradition it cannot be handed down Krishnamurti From the book Krishnamurti s Journal

content: There is lots of talk in the nutrition sphere of how humans are meant to eat A lot of the assumptions are often based on fallacies such as gorillas are our close relatives and they eat mostly greens so we should too or an ox eats grass and is strong so we should eat grass to be strong While grass will make an ox strong it s because an ox is designed to eat grass The bacteria in the rumen of an ox will turn grasses into fats and proteins that will fuel the animal and help it grow large But we are not ruminants We don t have a rumen I decided to put together some facts about the human digestive system to help paint an idea of what I believe they tell us about which foods are species appropriate foods for humans Let s also not forget that flavour plays a huge role in telling us which foods are best for us Humans love sweets while most other animals don t There is a reason for that and our reliance on simple sugars is a massive evolutionaly advantage Not medical advice ylifestyle y yfood motivation yliving yeating fam journey ist ie

content: York Pennslyvania is a historic American town on the Susquehanna River about an hour north of Baltimore and two hours west of Philadelphia There is archeological evidence of a food gathering in the area between 12 000 and 14 000 years ago Before the arrival of the British French and Dutch the area was inhabited by the Algonquians Susquehannocks and Shawnee tribes York was laid on orders by the Penn family as the first city west of the Susquehanna River in 1741 On the lamb from British troops in 1777 the American Continental Congress shaped the birth of the new nation in York The founding fathers drafted and approved the Articles of Confederation in York In the mid 19th century William C Goodridge son of a slave who became a successful York businessman started operating one of the most important stops on the Underground Railroad Goodridge and others spent decades whisking runaway slaves through the county toward Canada During the American Civil War Confederate troops successfully breached the town on the eve of the Battle of Gettysburg and forced the retreat of a small Union force Union troops stymie the Confederate advance by burning the Susquehanna River Bridge in Wrightsville In the early 20th century York became a hub for industry specializing in fabricated metal products the population diversified and quadrupled in a few decades These days York is known for its gorgeous pastoral scenery quaint atmosphere and preserved historic buildings Listed by Allison Altman This stunning 1920 s home in The Avenues has been beautifully updated and restored Lovely corner lot with fenced in back yard and patio Kitchen features abundant beautiful cabinetry and gorgeous butcher block counters stainless appliances and plenty of space for an island or kitchen table Outlets and light switches have been updated with period appropriate replica Updated bathrooms are fresh and compliment the home s character Original hardwood floors throughout showoff ornate inlays and herringbone patterns This home has 4 spacious bedrooms on the 2nd floor 1 full and 1 half bath You will love every inch of this well loved and beautifully designed home

content: Scientists at the University of Tokyo are bringing us one step closer by crafting a robotic finger surrounded by living human skin The method not only gave a robotic finger skin like texture but also water repellent and self healing capabilities To craft the skin the team first submerged the robotic finger in a cylinder filled with a solution of collagen and human dermal fibroblasts the two main components that make up the skin s connective tissues Takeuchi says the study s success lies within the natural shrinking tendency of this collagen and fibroblast mixture which shrank and tightly conformed to the finger Like paint primers this layer provided a uniform foundation for the next coat of cells human epidermal keratinocytes to stick to These cells make up 90 of the outermost layer of skin giving the robot a skin like texture and moisture retaining barrier properties The crafted skin had enough strength and elasticity to bear the dynamic movements as the robotic finger curled and stretched The outermost layer was thick enough to be lifted with tweezers and repelled water When wounded the crafted skin could even self heal like humans with the help of a collagen bandage which gradually morphed into the skin and withstood repeated joint movements The developed skin is much weaker than natural skin and can t survive long without constant nutrient supply and waste removal source sciencedaily com releases 2022 06 220609131938 htmDOI doi org 10 1016 j matt 2022 05 019Join bae community Join bae community

content: I lost count of how many times I missed a step and fell scraping my knee I wasn t stunned at all about how much it pained me But I found the peace I have been waiting for My everlasting desire has finally come to me For quite some time I kept on traipsing down memory lane The battles I fought the wounds I took the scars they left Nonetheless thank you for everything darling Thank you for the times we shared the moments I feel loved Thank you for letting go when I couldn t let go Perhaps our love was true but our story has no happy ending Please know that regret didn t occur once for I cherished you truly But our story was messed up it wasn t wrapped up nicely And yes I feel sorry for the times lost that cannot be rewritten I hope one day I ll still be able to read the happy ending But I collected moments rather than woes and tears I will treasure the laughter rather than the sorrows of our complex love If in the afterlife our paths will cross once more I wish we ll have the chance to greet each other and more But our story stops here although I wish it ll never end Thank you for letting go although I wish it ll be mended For now I say adieu Let s say I am high that this suddenly popped up lol I m gonna edit it or rewrite it later etc if I m in a nice mood art

content: Lahangan Sweet is a spot in Bali that definitely deserves your attention We fell in love with this place as soon as the view revealed in front of us But if you don t pick the right time and weather you might not see this beautiful view so we prepared some tips for you 1 Take 3 4 days in Amed for snorkelling and other activities including visiting Lahangan Sweet 2 You can clearly see the mountain from the town so definitely check every morning if it s visible and good enough for you to go If not leave for the next day 3 What time to go This spot is beautiful from sunrise to midday to sunset We re not early risers so we went in the middle of the day and it was amazing But if you want to avoid the clouds and the fog around the mountain sunrise would be better 4 The road is mostly uphill but it s very well made so it s definitely possible to go with a motorcycle As you get closer to the location tho there is a small steep and rough road so if you re not comfortable riding there just park before and walk it up for 10 min Is Lahangan Sweet in your list daily life goals

pCo: nature mountain outer space
content: Night sky as Milky Way and Andromeda galaxiesFour billion years from now our galaxy the Milky Way will collide with our large spiraled neighbor Andromeda The galaxies as we know them will not survive In fact our solar system is going to outlive our galaxy At that point the sun will not yet be a red giant star but it will have grown bright enough to roast Earth s surface Any life forms still there though will be treated to some pretty spectacular cosmic choreography The stars involved are sufficiently far apart that it is improbable that any of them will individually collide Some stars will be ejected from the resulting galaxy often nicknamed Milkomeda A description of what s happening in the images above 1st image Present day 2nd Image In 1 9 billion years the disk of the approaching Andromeda galaxy is noticeably larger 3rd image In 2 47 billion years Andromeda fills the field of view 4th image In 3 84 billion years the sky is ablaze with new star formation 5th image In 3 9 billion years star formation continues 6th image In 4 27 billion years Andromeda is tidally stretched and the Milky Way becomes warped 7th image In 5 5 billion years the cores of the Milky Way and Andromeda appear as a pair of bright lobes 8th image In 7 billion years the merged galaxies form a huge elliptical galaxy its bright core dominating the nighttime sky Follow us voyagersFrom NASA ESA Z Levay and R van der Marel STScI T Hallas and A Mellinger s s lover nomer photo physicist nomers engine galaxy

content: Skygazers will today witness the strawberry moon the second among the four consecutive supermoons this year Although there is no specific definition of a supermoon the term refers to a full moon that appears larger and brighter than on other days due to its proximity to Earth in its orbit The moon in its orbit will be at its closest point to Earth at 7 51 am Eastern Daylight Time 5 22 pm IST and will appear like a supermoon The satellite will come within 222 238 miles of Earth on Tuesday which is about 16 000 miles closer than its average distance The moon is likely to be about 10 percent brighter than the regular full moon According to NASA June s full moon will also be the lowest full moon of 2022 hovering at around 23 3 degrees above the horizon Link in IG stories

content: Did you know that one bowl of cherries contains three grams of dietary fibre 10 of a women s RDA and just 20 cherries make up 18 of a woman s RDA of Vitamin C swipe to find out more by scanning the QR card last week the team invited me down for their campaign the talk had a focus around amenorrhea which is the absence of a period amongst women of all ages Soo if you don t have a period granted your not on any form of hormones then that s pantsssss sisters They conducted a study which showed that a large percentage of women were not aware of the menstral period rather than the actual bleed and the importance of having a period There are two types of amenorrhea the most problematic being secondary When I had my eating disorder I developed secondary amenorrhea due to my restriction and overtraining Unfortunately I normalised not having a period because I didn t actually like having a period my mum was of course worried at such an early age to have years and years with no period I was seen by consultants and dieticians which often disregarded it because I was young and not wanting to become pregnant any time soon This campaign highlights how important it is whether that is the case or not Your period is not only important if you are planning on having child but it governs alot of functions to have a healthy body I think it s defo worth having a read about the campaign I thoroughly enjoyed attending the talk as it had a personal touch on me 333 it s also great for those girls currently suffering with amenorrhea ad

content: Want to train smarter When you weight train you want to be able to train with a high amount of intensity for hypertrophy You will always be able to maintain a higher training intensity throughout 4 5 exercises rather than 6 Less is more Don t overdo it with volume or you ll under do it with intensity Each session I aim to do 4 exercises within 3 4 sets Each set you do should be hard without compromising your form you should have 1 3 reps left in the tank Just because you have 4 sets of 10 reps doesn t mean you stop on 10 If you know you could have done some more reps do more reps It s not meant to be easy And you re not doing yourself favours by putting the weights down early Pick them back up and keep going 4 exercises 3 4 sets Max effort Consistent rest between sets More time recovering between sessions Repeat

content: WEEK 8 CHECK IN We got a new low weigh in gang So week 8 was a goooooood week When I said laser focus I meant it This week has been all about ticking the boxes and it s paid off because today was a nice new low weigh in This is honestly the first week of my dieting phase that I ve actually felt GREAT I feel awake energised confident in myself and happy with the progress I m making For a while I questioned myself and wondered if this was what I really wanted but now it s starting to pay off and I m so excited to push just a little bit more This is the most consistent I ve ever been it s all down to keeping myself accountable with a coach project sparkes without that I wouldn t have got this far 6 weeks 4 days till my holiday the end is in sight and I can t wait to see what more I can achieve Side note Dieting is not easy There s no way to sugar coat is It s just not You need to be in the right frame of mind and you need to be willing to work for it Only you can make the changes but once you do I bet you ll be so glad you never gave up Coaching enquires link in bio mirror ness nessmotivation nesspage

content: Change of Direction Workout 6 Lateral Movement Exercises To Develop Lateral Speed and Ability To Cut Change DirectionGreat for lateral demanding sports like Tennis Baseball Football Combat Sports Handball etc LATERAL FORCE PRODUCTION These drills teach your body to cut efficiently hard fast These drills teach you to 1st ABSORB force then redirect that same force energy outwardly at a moments notice Everything s in the details You have to make sure you re being reactive to the ground keeping your movements sharp and quick If you re able to absorb force correctly and efficiently then whenever you go to change direction cut juke or steal a base burst defend etc You will be 10x more explosive in the lateral direction It s allllll about movement You have to be able to move You have to teach the body to be able to move efficiently when training in order to have efficient movements when playingWhen doing these drills STAY ON THE BALL OF YOUR FOOT Because this is the way you play and this method strengthens the ankles more efficiently The stronger the ankles the more force you put into the ground the faster you go FORCE SPEED It s physics training training training training

content: 1936 WHITE MODEL 706 GLACIER NATIONAL PARK TOUR BUSGlacier National Park first opened the Going to the Sun road on July 15 1933 and began offering a Red Bus Tour shortly thereafter an attraction that continues to this day Produced by the White Motor Company of Cleveland Ohio this Model 706 bus is powered by a 318 CI 16A flathead 6 cylinder engine With seating up to 17 passengers a large sliding canvas top allows for unobstructed views Designed by Count Alexis de Sakhnoffsky this bus is No 363 of roughly 500 built in total for the U S National Parks Originally serving at Yellowstone National Park this bus has been restored in period correct Glacier National Parks Reds livery the red color originally derived from the ripe Mountain Ash Berry in Glacier National Park with a tan interior and red and black steel wheels with a bright center cap Complete with a cargo area behind the rearmost row of seats the entire vehicle presents largely in as new condition the highly detailed exhibition sustaining from the engine and engine bay throughout the interior and exterior surfaces The front end is signature White with a tall chrome vertical bar grille underscored by a chrome bumper with a gentle center dip allowing for full grille exposure large twin headlights mounted to the black fenders flank the scene Inside atop the seatbacks chrome grab bars span the width of the seats providing some degree of stability for passengers likely a welcome addition back in the days of traversing the curvy roads to the top of the world Interestingly the tan headliner is detailed with chrome ribs that somewhat visually mimic the grab bars The restored dashboard features refurbished gauges and beautiful switches while out back barn doors allow access to the rear quarters Picture and text ers ers daily fun post pic ofinstagram tagram porn lifestyle ofinsta cars cool
